:INFO
Reduce Decision Fatigue with Weekly Planning
Every decision drains mental energy. A Sunday planning ritual pre-makes hundreds of small decisions about meals, clothes, and tasks so weekdays run on autopilot and cognitive load stays low.

:COUNTER.half
35000 Decisions
Estimated decisions an adult makes per day
|
:COUNTER.half
90 Minutes
Typical Sunday planning session to pre-decide the week

:PATH
Plan Meals
Description: Choose seven dinners and prep a shopping list on Sunday. Pre-cook grains, roast vegetables, and portion snacks. Remove the what should I eat question from every day.

:PATH
Plan Tasks and Priorities
Description: Review your task backlog and assign specific tasks to specific days. Do not leave the week open. A pre-decided task list removes the daily choice of what to work on.

:PATH
Set Defaults
Description: Establish standing defaults for recurring choices: the same breakfast every weekday, a uniform work outfit rotation, a fixed workout time. Defaults require zero decision-making once established.

:CHECKLIST
Weekly Planning Checklist
[ ] Review last week: what worked, what did not
[ ] Set three priority outcomes for the coming week
[ ] Assign meals and prep grocery list
[ ] Assign tasks to specific days in your planner
[ ] Lay out clothes or set outfit rotation
[ ] Charge devices and prep bag the night before Monday

:NOTE
The goal is not rigidity but pre-commitment. Having a plan you modify is always better than having no plan and deciding under pressure each morning.
